juilliard string quartet events at stanford juilliard string quartet facebook twitter email print add to calendar one of the world's most celebrated enduring chamber ensembles returns to stanford with its newest member violinist joseph lin the centuries spanning program includes a seminal work by mozart dedicated to haydn stravinsky's three pieces for string quartet flavorful miniatures that range from adaptations of russian tunes to music inspired by an english music hall clown little tich and janacek's passionate muscular first quartet inspired by tolstoy's story the kreutzer sonata a work that affected the composer deeply program stravinsky three pieces for string quartet 1914 rev 1918 janacek quartet no 1 kreutzer sonata jw 7 8 1923 mozart string quartet no 18 in a major k 464 1785 generously supported by john and mary felstiner when sunday december 4 2011 2 30 pm where dinkelspiel auditorium map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags performance music arts sponsor stanford lively arts contact 650 725 arts 2787 livelyarts stanford edu admission reserved seating $48 56 permalink http events stanford edu events 284 28473 more info last modified november 15 2011
